--- TESTCASE Update Employee - Success - 204 No Content

--- HTTP
## TEST-EXPECT-STATUS: [204]
PUT {{ApiBaseUrl}}{{EmployeesSection}}/{{EmployeeId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mgr.",
  "firstName": "James",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "phone": "+421 987 654 321",
  "email": "james.smith@example.com"
}

--- END


--- TESTCASE Update Employee - Verify Changes - 200 OK

--- HTTP
## TEST-EXPECT-STATUS: [200]
## TEST-HAS-BODY
GET {{ApiBaseUrl}}{{EmployeesSection}}/{{EmployeeId}}

--- TEST
await tp.Test("Employee should reflect updated values.", async () =>
{
    dynamic body = await tp.Response.GetBodyAsExpandoAsync();
    Equal("Mgr.", (string)body.title);
    Equal("James", (string)body.firstName);
    Equal("Smith", (string)body.lastName);
    Equal("+421 987 654 321", (string)body.phone);
    Equal("james.smith@example.com", (string)body.email);
});

--- END


--- TESTCASE Update Employee - Nonexistent Employee - 404 Not Found

--- HTTP
## TEST-EXPECT-STATUS: [404]
PUT {{ApiBaseUrl}}{{EmployeesSection}}/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith"
}

--- END


